Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'TFCC lesion' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Traumatic' radio button is enabled
And 'Degenerative' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Traumatic' radio button
Then 'Type I A: central perforation of the TFCC' radio button is enabled
And 'Type I B: ulnar avulsion with or without distal ulnar fracture involving the styloid and/or foveal attachement' radio button is enabled
And 'Type I C: distal avulsion of the TFCC involving ulnotriquetral and ulnolunate ligaments' radio button is enabled
And 'Type I D: radial avulsion of the TFCC with or without sigmoid notch fracture' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Degenerative' radio button
Then 'Type II A: TFCC wear with thinning/fraying, no perforation' radio button is enabled
And 'Type II B: type II A with lunate, triquetral and/or ulnar chondromalacia' radio button is enabled
And 'Type II C: central perforation with or without chondromalacia' radio button is enabled
And 'Type II D: LT ligament perforation with or without features of Type II A, B, C' radio button is enabled
And 'Type II E: ulnocarpal arthritis with or without features of Type II A, B, C, D' radio button is enabled
